_note: I'm not quite sure how straightforwardly it applies to Rust because of LLVM, but anyways..._

Similar .debug_gdb_scripts issue has been identified as a bug in GNU linker (https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=21459). 

As a workaround (by Nick Clifton) a linker script can be provided to `gcc` or `ld`:

```
SECTIONS
{
  .debug_gdb_scripts BLOCK(__section_alignment__) (NOLOAD) :
  {
    *(.debug_gdb_scripts)
  }
}
INSERT AFTER .debug_types;
```

To use with gcc, run `gcc -Wl,-T,fix-debug-gdb-scripts.ld`. Or when using the linker `ld -T debug.ld`.
